HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 401
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Tessa Statom, 2025
Salutatorian of Collinwood High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Tessa Statom is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
Salutatorian of the 2025 graduating class at Collinwood High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Statom has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Tessa Statom has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Statom's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for her future success at Bethel University, where she will study secondary education with an
emphasis in mathematics and play as a member of the Bethel women's basketball team; and
WHEREAS, her noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for her
parents, Lindsay and Mark Statom, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Statom's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor the 2025 Collinwood High School
